President Biden delivered a speech in the East Room, thanking Congress and members of both parties for passing the COVID-19 Hate Crimes Act. He emphasized the importance of unity and standing against hate and racism. The President acknowledged the increase in hate crimes against Asian Americans and pledged to combat xenophobia and hate crimes. He highlighted the need for resources, training, and improved reporting of hate crimes, as well as changing hearts and speaking out against hate. President Biden also recognized the families of Heather Heyer and Khalid Jabara, whose tragic deaths motivated the passage of the law. He closed by emphasizing the unique nature of the United States and the importance of upholding its principles of equality and justice. The President then signed the bill into law.